# Google Drive sign-in + Picker for the lab apps (mind, setlist).
#
# The voidstar-sh project's own client id + Picker key are baked into
# src/lib/qualia/google-config.js as defaults, so the deployed site works with
# no config. Set these ONLY to override those defaults for a self-host /
# different deployment — copy to `.env` (gitignored) for local dev, or set as
# build-time env vars in your host (Cloudflare Pages / Netlify / Vercel). Both
# are PUBLIC identifiers — they ship in the client bundle and are protected by
# the OAuth origin + API-key referrer/API restrictions you configure in the
# Google Cloud console, not by secrecy.

# OAuth 2.0 Web client id (APIs & Services → Credentials). Register
# https://voidstar.sh (and http://127.0.0.1:4321 for dev) as authorized
# JavaScript origins. Scope used: drive.file (non-sensitive — no security
# assessment required).
PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# API key for the Google Picker API. Restrict it to HTTP referrers
# (https://voidstar.sh/*, dev http://127.0.0.1:4321/*) and to the Google Picker
# API only. Enables the "pick from Drive…" document import.
PUBLIC_GOOGLE_PICKER_API_KEY=
